Beat the pudding mix and milk in a large bowl with a whisk for 2 minutes. Cover and refrigerate for 20 minutes. Spoon 1 tablespoon fudge topping into each pastry shell. Reserve 6 slices banana. Divide the remaining banana among the pastry shells. Spoon the pudding mixture into the pastry shells. Top each with 1/4 cup whipped cream and 1 slice reserved banana.